# Midnight Edge — Typography & Layout

All text and layout spacing must consume Midnight Edge tokens from [`src/config/theme.ts`](src/config/theme.ts).

## Typography — Inter Only

All text must use the Inter font family via `toTextStyle()` — never `fontFamily: "System"` or hardcoded sizes.

Headings must use weight 700–800 with tight negative letter-spacing from the token definition.

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `typography.displayLg` | Hero displays, splash headlines |
| `typography.headlineLg` | Section titles (tablet/desktop) |
| `typography.headlineLgMobile` | Section titles on mobile |
| `typography.headlineMd` | Subsection headings |
| `typography.bodyLg` | Lead paragraphs |
| `typography.bodyMd` | Default body copy |
| `typography.labelMd` | Form labels, nav items |
| `typography.labelSm` | Badges, metadata, category tags (uppercase) |

Metadata fields, badges, and category tags must use `typography.labelSm` exclusively — this enforces uppercase with 0.05em tracking.

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded typography, System font
<Text style={{ fontSize: 28, fontWeight: "700", letterSpacing: -0.5 }}>
  Trending Styles
</Text>
<Text style={{ fontSize: 11, color: "#999" }}>Premium</Text>

// GOOD — token-driven Inter typography
import { toTextStyle } from "@/config/theme";
import { useTheme } from "@/hooks/useTheme";

const SectionHeader = ({ title, tag }: { title: string; tag: string }): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <View style={{ gap: theme.spacing.stackSm }}>
      <Text style={[toTextStyle(theme.typography.headlineLgMobile), { color: theme.colors.text.primary }]}>
        {title}
      </Text>
      <Text style={[toTextStyle(theme.typography.labelSm), { color: theme.colors.primary.dim }]}>
        {tag}
      </Text>
    </View>
  );
};
```

## Layout Spacing Tokens

Use layout spacing tokens — never arbitrary pixel values for structural spacing.

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `spacing.containerMargin` | 20px | Horizontal screen inset |
| `spacing.gutter` | 16px | Column gap in grid layouts |
| `spacing.stackSm` | 8px | Tight vertical stacking |
| `spacing.stackMd` | 16px | Default vertical stacking |
| `spacing.stackLg` | 24px | Loose vertical stacking |
| `spacing.sectionGap` | 40px | Gap between major sections |

## 4-Column Fluid Layout

Mobile layouts follow a 4-column fluid grid mental model:

- Apply `spacing.containerMargin` (20px) as horizontal padding on screen containers
- Divide remaining width into 4 columns separated by `spacing.gutter` (16px)
- Full-width elements span all 4 columns; half-width spans 2 columns

```tsx
// GOOD — container margin + section gap
const ScreenContainer = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <View
      style={{
        flex: 1,
        paddingHorizontal: theme.spacing.containerMargin,
        gap: theme.spacing.sectionGap,
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </View>
  );
};
```

## Masonry & Stat Pills

Photo discovery streams and lifestyle lookbook layouts must use **asymmetrical masonry grids** — not uniform row heights.

Horizontal stat indicators (XP, distance, user ratings) must use **full pill** border radius:

```tsx
// GOOD — stat pill with full radius
<View
  style={{
    flexDirection: "row",
    alignItems: "center",
    paddingHorizontal: theme.spacing.stackMd,
    paddingVertical: theme.spacing.stackSm,
    borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.full,
    backgroundColor: theme.colors.depth.level1,
    borderColor: theme.colors.border.level1,
    borderWidth: 1,
  }}
>
  <Text style={[toTextStyle(theme.typography.labelMd), { color: theme.colors.gamification.emerald }]}>
    +120 XP
  </Text>
</View>
```

## NativeWind Parity

When using Tailwind classes, prefer mapped utilities from [`tailwind.config.js`](tailwind.config.js): `text-headline-lg-mobile`, `p-container-margin`, `rounded-full`, `bg-depth-1`.
